Whisk together soy sauce, lime juice, water, sugar, garlic, and chile paste in medium bowl. Pour 3 tablespoons into resealable plastic bag. Cover and chill remaining dressing for salad. Add steak to bag, seal, and turn to coat. Chill 30 minutes. Heat grill or broiler to medium-high. Grill steak 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, for medium-rare. (Thermometer should register 145 degrees F.) Let rest 5 minutes and slice thinly at an angle, across the grain. Toss together greens, basil, and cilantro in large bowl. Evenly divide among 4 plates. Sprinkle with onions, cucumbers, and carrots. Top with steak, drizzle with dressing, and sprinkle with peanuts.